cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortTable
cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortTable.description: This table contains the TNPP port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTTNPPPortEntry.description: Entries in the TNPP port configuration table.

tnppPCfgPortNumber.name: tnppPCfgPortNumber
tnppPCfgPortNumber.description: Port Number of the TNPP port.

tnppPCfgPortType.name: tnppPCfgPortType
tnppPCfgPortType.description: Specifies the type of access protocol for this port.

tnppPCfgPortSpeed.name: tnppPCfgPortSpeed
tnppPCfgPortSpeed.description: Specifies port speed in bits per second. speed300 : 300 bits per second. speed1200 : 1200 bits per second. speed2400 : 2400 bits per second. speed4800 : 4800 bits per second. speed9600 : 9600 bits per second. speed19200 : 19200 bits per second.

tnppPCfgCallControl.name: tnppPCfgCallControl
tnppPCfgCallControl.description: Specifies the mode for X.25 call generation. dtr - X.25 call is generated when DTR is up. Connection type between TNPP PAD and Paging Terminal is DTR. dataDrv - X.25 call is generated on incoming data. Connection type between TNPP PAD and Paging Terminal is SIMP. powerOn - X.25 call is generated on Node Boot/Power On. Connection type between TNPP PAD and Paging Terminal is SIMP. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgCRCOption.name: tnppPCfgCRCOption
tnppPCfgCRCOption.description: Specifies the CRC option. normal - 2 bytes binary CRC. transp - 4 bytes ASCII CRC. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgTANControl.name: tnppPCfgTANControl
tnppPCfgTANControl.description: Specifies whether to accept control characters(ACK/NAK) in the frame. mps2000Mode - Do not accept embedded control characters in the frame. unipageMode - Accept embedded control characters in the frame. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgCANReports.name: tnppPCfgCANReports
tnppPCfgCANReports.description: Specifies whether to log reports generated by TNPP PAD. no - Reports generated due to CANcel frame will not be logged. yes - Reports generated due to CANcel frame will be logged which will be controlled by node parameter. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgRSCount.name: tnppPCfgRSCount
tnppPCfgRSCount.description: TNPP PAD port will flow control the X.25 channel when the number of RSed frames on hold remains at or above the configured value of this parameter. Specifies the limit for RS support by TNPP PAD.

tnppPCfgMaxRSCount.name: tnppPCfgMaxRSCount
tnppPCfgMaxRSCount.description: TNPP PAD port will stop transmission of any new frame to the paging terminal if the number of frames on hold remains above the value of this parameter. Transmission of control frames and retransmission of RS timed out frames will continue. Specifies the maximum number of RS that can be received before the TNPP PAD stops transmission.

tnppPCfgRSSupport.name: tnppPCfgRSSupport
tnppPCfgRSSupport.description: Specifies whether to respond with RS to local paging terminal in case of X25 link being blocked. no - RS is not transmitted. yes - RS is transmitted. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgAutocallMnemonic.name: tnppPCfgAutocallMnemonic
tnppPCfgAutocallMnemonic.description: This parameter refers to the remote address which will be called by the TNPP PAD port. Specifies the Mnemonic Address for Autocall.

tnppPCfgAutocallTimeout.name: tnppPCfgAutocallTimeout
tnppPCfgAutocallTimeout.description: This parameter is the time interval in seconds between call attempts when auto calling. Specifies the time value for retrying AUTOCALL in seconds.

tnppPCfgMaxAutocallAttempt.name: tnppPCfgMaxAutocallAttempt
tnppPCfgMaxAutocallAttempt.description: Specifies the number of Autocall attempts. 0 - No Autocall retry limit.

tnppPCfgProtectionLevel.name: tnppPCfgProtectionLevel
tnppPCfgProtectionLevel.description: This specifies the level of data or connection protection which will be applied to calls to or from this port. The actual level for a call will be negotiated to the lesser of this level and the level configured for the other end of the call. none - No protection. cpOnly - Connection protection only. fullDcp - Full data and connection protection. nc - Skipped during configuration.

tnppPCfgReconnTimeout.name: tnppPCfgReconnTimeout
tnppPCfgReconnTimeout.description: This specifies the number of seconds that DCP on the originating side will wait between reconnection attempts.

tnppPCfgMaxReconnAttempt.name: tnppPCfgMaxReconnAttempt
tnppPCfgMaxReconnAttempt.description: This specifies the number of times that DCP on the orginating side will attempt to reconnect before clearing the call. If the value is zero no attempt to reconnect will be made.

tnppPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: tnppPCfgElectricalInterfaceType
tnppPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

tnppPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.name: tnppPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
tnppPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

tnppPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOpti.name: tnppPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
tnppPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOpti.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

tnppPGenStatTable.name: tnppPGenStatTable
tnppPGenStatTable.description: This table contains the port statistics general parameters.

tnppPGenStatEntry.name: tnppPGenStatEntry
tnppPGenStatEntry.description: Entries in the TNPP port statistics general parameters table.

tnppPGStatPortNumber.name: tnppPGStatPortNumber
tnppPGStatPortNumber.description: Port Number of the TNPP port.

tnppPGStatPortType.name: tnppPGStatPortType
tnppPGStatPortType.description: This indicates the type of access protocol for this port.

tnppPGStatPortStatus.name: tnppPGStatPortStatus
tnppPGStatPortStatus.description: This indicates the operational status of the port. disabled : port is disabled. up : port is up. na : Value not available.

tnppPGStatPortSpeed.name: tnppPGStatPortSpeed
tnppPGStatPortSpeed.description: This indicates the port speed in bits per second.

tnppPGStatPortUtilIn.name: tnppPGStatPortUtilIn
tnppPGStatPortUtilIn.description: This indicates the port utilization for the line to port direction.

tnppPGStatPortUtilOut.name: tnppPGStatPortUtilOut
tnppPGStatPortUtilOut.description: This indicates the port utilization for the port to line direction.

tnppPGStatParityErrors.name: tnppPGStatParityErrors
tnppPGStatParityErrors.description: This indicates the number of parity errors counted by the I/O driver.

tnppPGStatOverrunErrors.name: tnppPGStatOverrunErrors
tnppPGStatOverrunErrors.description: This indicates number of overrun errors detected by the I/O driver.

tnppPGStatFramingErrors.name: tnppPGStatFramingErrors
tnppPGStatFramingErrors.description: This indicates number of framing errors detected by the I/O driver.

tnppPGStatLocalDTEState.name: tnppPGStatLocalDTEState
tnppPGStatLocalDTEState.description: This indicates the local DTE state. active - DTE is active. down - DTE is down. na - Value not available.

tnppPGStatRemoteDTEState.name: tnppPGStatRemoteDTEState
tnppPGStatRemoteDTEState.description: This indicates the remote DTE state. active - DTE is active. down - DTE is down. na - Value not available.

tnppPGStatRemotePadQ.name: tnppPGStatRemotePadQ
tnppPGStatRemotePadQ.description: This indicates the size of the remote TNPP PAD queue.

tnppPGStatLocalTerminalQ.name: tnppPGStatLocalTerminalQ
tnppPGStatLocalTerminalQ.description: This indicates the size of the Local Terminal queue.

tnppPGStatReadyQ.name: tnppPGStatReadyQ
tnppPGStatReadyQ.description: This indicates the size of the Ready Queue.

tnppPGStatHoldQ.name: tnppPGStatHoldQ
tnppPGStatHoldQ.description: This indicates the size of the Hold Queue.

tnppPDataSummaryStatTable.name: tnppPDataSummaryStatTable
tnppPDataSummaryStatTable.description: This table contains the TNPP port statistics data summary parameters.

tnppPDataSummaryStatEntry.name: tnppPDataSummaryStatEntry
tnppPDataSummaryStatEntry.description: Entries in the TNPP port statistics data summary table.

tnppPDSStatPortNumber.name: tnppPDSStatPortNumber
tnppPDSStatPortNumber.description: Port Number of the TNPP port.

tnppPDSStatTotalCharIn.name: tnppPDSStatTotalCharIn
tnppPDSStatTotalCharIn.description: This indicates the total number of characters that have been received by the port.

tnppPDSStatTotalCharOut.name: tnppPDSStatTotalCharOut
tnppPDSStatTotalCharOut.description: This indicates the total number of characters that have been transmitted by the port.

tnppPDSStatTotalFramesIn.name: tnppPDSStatTotalFramesIn
tnppPDSStatTotalFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of frames that have been received by the port.

tnppPDSStatTotalFramesOut.name: tnppPDSStatTotalFramesOut
tnppPDSStatTotalFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of frames that have been transmitted by the port.

tnppPDSStatCharInPerSec.name: tnppPDSStatCharInPerSec
tnppPDSStatCharInPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which characters have been received by the port per second.

tnppPDSStatCharOutPerSec.name: tnppPDSStatCharOutPerSec
tnppPDSStatCharOutPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which characters have been transmitted by the port per second.

tnppPDSStatFramesInPerSec.name: tnppPDSStatFramesInPerSec
tnppPDSStatFramesInPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which frames have been received by the port per second.

tnppPDSStatFramesOutPerSec.name: tnppPDSStatFramesOutPerSec
tnppPDSStatFramesOutPerSec.description: This indicates the rate at which frames have been transmitted by the port per second.

tnppPFrameSummaryStatTable.name: tnppPFrameSummaryStatTable
tnppPFrameSummaryStatTable.description: This table contains the TNPP port statistics frame summary parameters.

tnppPFrameSummaryStatEntry.name: tnppPFrameSummaryStatEntry
tnppPFrameSummaryStatEntry.description: Entries in the TNPP port statistics frame summary table.

tnppPFSStatPortNumber.name: tnppPFSStatPortNumber
tnppPFSStatPortNumber.description: Port number of the TNPP port.

tnppPFSStatLinkState.name: tnppPFSStatLinkState
tnppPFSStatLinkState.description: This indicates the current link state. init - Initialization state. awaitEnqResp - Await enquiry response state. ready - Ready to communicate state. transmitting - Transmitting state. transmitResponse - Transmit response state. na - Value not available.

tnppPFSStatCRCErrors.name: tnppPFSStatCRCErrors
tnppPFSStatCRCErrors.description: This indicates the total number of TNPP frames received with Cyclic Redundancy Check errors .

tnppPFSStatLinkFramingErrors.name: tnppPFSStatLinkFramingErrors
tnppPFSStatLinkFramingErrors.description: This indicates the total number of TNPP framing errors occured (Invalid Header, Invalid Control character, Frame Size Exceeded, Incomplete Frame, etc.,) .

tnppPFSStatProtocolErrors.name: tnppPFSStatProtocolErrors
tnppPFSStatProtocolErrors.description: This indicates the number of protocol errors due to unexpected events.

tnppPFSStatACKFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatACKFramesIn
tnppPFSStatACKFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of Acknowledgment frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatACKFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatACKFramesOut
tnppPFSStatACKFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of Acknowledgment frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatNAKFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatNAKFramesIn
tnppPFSStatNAKFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of Negative Acknowledgment frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatNAKFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatNAKFramesOut
tnppPFSStatNAKFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of Negative Acknowledgment frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatRSFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatRSFramesIn
tnppPFSStatRSFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of Request to Stop frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatRSFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatRSFramesOut
tnppPFSStatRSFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of Request to Stop frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatCANFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatCANFramesIn
tnppPFSStatCANFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of CANcel report frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatCANFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatCANFramesOut
tnppPFSStatCANFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of CANcel report frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatEOTFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatEOTFramesIn
tnppPFSStatEOTFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of End of Transmission frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatEOTFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatEOTFramesOut
tnppPFSStatEOTFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of End of Transmission frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatENQFramesIn.name: tnppPFSStatENQFramesIn
tnppPFSStatENQFramesIn.description: This indicates the total number of Enquiry frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatENQFramesOut.name: tnppPFSStatENQFramesOut
tnppPFSStatENQFramesOut.description: This indicates the total number of Enquiry frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatDataFramesInPassed.name: tnppPFSStatDataFramesInPassed
tnppPFSStatDataFramesInPassed.description: This indicates the total number of valid data frames received by the port.

tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutPassed.name: tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutPassed
tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutPassed.description: This indicates the total number of valid data frames transmitted by the port.

tnppPFSStatDataFramesInDiscarded.name: tnppPFSStatDataFramesInDiscarded
tnppPFSStatDataFramesInDiscarded.description: This indicates the total number of data frames received by the port and discarded.

tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutDiscarded.name: tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutDiscarded
tnppPFSStatDataFramesOutDiscarded.description: This indicates the total number of data frames transmitted by the port and discarded.

cdx6500ContTNPPPortTable.name: cdx6500ContTNPPPortTable

tnppPContPortNumber.description: Port number of the TNPP port.

tnppPContPortControl.name: tnppPContPortControl
tnppPContPortControl.description: Control operations for the specified TNPP port. boot - Boots the TNPP Port. enable - Enables the TNPP Port. disable - Disables the TNPP Port. busyout - Busyout the TNPP Port. resetstats - Resets the TNPP port statistics.
